I have put a new version of the Windows binary installer 
(Cantera155.msi) on the sourceforge site.  It should be complete now, 
and it contains a powerpoint presentation showing how to install 
Cantera.  This version also uses the new and very stable equilibrium 
solver for problems with specified T and P.  If you have had problems 
with the old solver, try this one.

By the way, the machine that hosted the Cantera website is down.  To 
get to the sourceforge site, go to 
http://sourceforge.net/projects/cantera.
